			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For the record, you DON'T need a skill of 155+ to make a bow.  The hickory bow with Hemp string, although not a great bow, is trivial at 16( thats sixteen ).  to make a bow simply combine a bow shaft and string in a fletching kit.  You can add a knife or plane to bows of elm or higher and cams do bows of oak and higher.  The following site is a very good place for bow and arrow making information.  It was instrumental in helping me acheive a skill of 202. The site is http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ewj/fletchguide.htm    It is a very good source for those looking to take up fletching and bow making.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
